---
import Layout from '../../layout/Layout.astro';
import ProjectBanner from '../../components/ProjectBanner.astro';
import StanBanner from '../../assets/stan-banner.svg';
import StanBannerDoodle from '../../assets/stan-banner-doodle.svg';
import ContentCard from '../../components/ContentCard.astro';
import CenterContainer from '../../components/CenterContainer.astro';
import Paragraph from '../../components/Paragraph.astro';
import Spacer from '../../components/Spacer.astro';
import DemoVideo from '../../components/DemoVideo.astro';
import { asset } from '../../utils/base-url';
---

<Layout>
	<CenterContainer>
		<ProjectBanner doodleId="stanDoodle">
			<StanBanner slot="logo" />
			<StanBannerDoodle slot="doodle" />
		</ProjectBanner>
		<ContentCard title="My Work At Stan">
			<div class="pad">
				<Paragraph heading="Four Years,Building Australia's Streaming Platform">
					For the past 4 years, I've been part of the six person team powering <b>Stan</b>,
					Australia's largest homegrown streaming service.
					<br />
					I maintain the core TV app running on 175+ platforms serving 1.6M+ users across smart TVs,
					game consoles, and set top boxes.
					<br />
					From the 2024 Olympics to daily binge watching, every stream on TV runs through code I've
					written.
				</Paragraph>
				<Spacer />
				<DemoVideo
					src={asset('stan.mp4')}
					poster={asset('stan-poster.jpg')}
					width={1280}
					height={720}
				/>
			</div>
			<div class="pad">
				<Paragraph heading="Open Source,Awards, and Big Wins">
					I contributed a <a
						href="https://github.com/shaka-project/shaka-player/pull/9066"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener"
						class="inline-link"
						>4x performance improvement to Google's open-source Shaka Player HLS parser</a
					>, work that earned the Nine Digital Annual Award for "No Stone Left Unturned" (one of
					only four awards given annually).
					<br />
					I led a device performance initiative that brought 2015+ legacy devices onto the latest
					app version, increasing platform coverage by 30%.
					<br />
					As a key contributor to the 2024 Olympics project, I rebuilt core navigation, improved
					app stability, and enhanced analytics and reporting under one of the highest traffic
					events of the year.
					<br />
					My work spans video playback engineering, performance optimisation, internal tooling,
					systems design and architecture. The focus: making Stan work flawlessly on extremely
					constrained hardware running ancient browser webviews.
				</Paragraph>
			</div>
			<div class="pad">
				<Paragraph heading="The Tech Stack">
					Built with React, TypeScript, and Redux running across Tizen, WebOS, WebMAF, and dozens
					of platforms.
					<br />
					Webpack handles the heavy lifting for 175+ device configurations each with unique quirks
					and limitations. Targeting devices all the way down to Chrome 38 and Safari 7.
					<br />
					I've built custom internal tooling around native tooling gaps, creating a unified dev
					experience across every platform.
					<br />
					It's the kind of infrastructure work that doesn't ship features but makes shipping
					features possible.
				</Paragraph>
			</div>
			<div class="pad">
				<Paragraph heading="Systems,Tools, and Team Impact">
					I build the infrastructure teams rely on. Testing pipelines for QA enabling robust video
					and ad testing across devices. Internal libraries for logging, performant animations,
					analytics, and error handling used across all platforms.
					<br />
					Performance work ran deep. Eliminated unnecessary React render cycles, migrated WebP to
					JPG for devices with software only decoders, preloaded fonts on browsers without the
					preload attribute, batched analytics on user idle, and built GPU optimised animation
					primitives that favour compositing over layout.
					<br />
					Refactored a monolithic codebase into a modular, functional and testable monorepo.
					<br />
					Mentored junior developers, hosted organisation wide tech talks, and represented
					developers in Stan's internal design system guild.
					<br />
					Conducted deep research into video storage, image rendering, and automated testing on
					constrained hardware.
					<br />
					My team won Best Teamwork at Nine Digital's Hack into History hackathon.
				</Paragraph>
			</div>

			<Spacer />
		</ContentCard>
		<Spacer triple />
	</CenterContainer>

	<style>
		.inline-link {
			color: var(--text);
			text-decoration: underline;
			text-decoration-thickness: 2px;
			text-underline-offset: 3px;
			transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
		}

		.pad {
			padding: 20px;
		}

		.inline-link:hover {
			opacity: 0.7;
		}
	</style>
</Layout>
